/// FACT TABLE — Core transaction-level sales data. One row = one order line. Contains all raw measures (revenue, profit, cost) and foreign keys linking to dimension tables. This is the central table of the star schema — all DAX measures are calculated from here. Do NOT use columns like product_name, region, sales_rep directly in visuals; use the corresponding Dim_ tables instead for proper filtering and slicing.
table Fact_Sales
	lineageTag: 5443636a-8137-4108-bb48-89c091218e17

	/// WHAT: Sum of all revenue across selected filters.
	/// LOGIC: SUM(revenue) where revenue = unit_price x quantity x (1 - discount_pct/100). Already pre-calculated in the source data.
	/// USE IN: KPI card (primary), Monthly Revenue vs Target combo chart (bar), Revenue by Region horizontal bar, Sales Rep leaderboard. This is the #1 commercial KPI — place top-left on every dashboard page.
	/// RAG TARGET: Green >95% of MYR 14M, Amber 85-95%, Red <85%.
	measure 'Total Revenue' = SUM(Fact_Sales[Revenue])
		formatString: #,##0.00
		displayFolder: Financial KPIs
		lineageTag: c3bb9519-183b-4e0b-a20e-8f0637364a78

	/// WHAT: Sum of all profit across selected filters.
	/// LOGIC: SUM(profit) where profit = revenue - (cost_price x quantity). Can be negative — 28.9% of orders are loss-making, which is a critical business signal.
	/// USE IN: KPI card (secondary), Category Revenue & Margin clustered bar, Sales Rep leaderboard. Pair with [Gross Margin %] to distinguish volume vs efficiency.
	/// RAG TARGET: Green >40% margin, Amber 35-40%, Red <35%.
	measure 'Total Profit' = SUM(Fact_Sales[Profit])
		formatString: #,##0.00
		displayFolder: Financial KPIs
		lineageTag: e8ebf986-af2a-4b10-9853-da5c193f4cd9

	/// WHAT: Overall profitability as a percentage of revenue.
	/// LOGIC: DIVIDE(Total Profit, Total Revenue). Returns 0 if revenue is zero (safe divide). Expressed as a decimal — format as percentage in visuals.
	/// USE IN: KPI card, Category breakdown bar (dual axis), Product treemap color encoding. A 40%+ margin is the benchmark. Accessories lead at 43.3%; Furniture trails at 37.6%.
	/// RAG TARGET: Green >40%, Amber 35-40%, Red <35%.
	/// NOTE: Blended 2024 actual = 40.7%.
	measure 'Gross Margin %' = DIVIDE([Total Profit], [Total Revenue], 0)
		formatString: 0.00%
		displayFolder: Financial KPIs
		lineageTag: e78a7047-b902-436c-b305-25c73563b398

	/// WHAT: The share of orders where actual revenue met or exceeded the order-level target revenue.
	/// LOGIC: Count orders where attainment_flag = 1 (revenue >= target_revenue), divided by total order count.
	/// USE IN: Gauge chart (primary use), Sales Rep leaderboard column, KPI card. Currently only 38.9% — a critical underperformance signal. Do NOT confuse with [Revenue vs Target] which compares total revenue sums.
	/// RAG TARGET: Green >90%, Amber 70-90%, Red <70%.
	/// WARNING: Only 777 of 2,000 orders hit target in 2024.
	measure 'Target Attainment %' = DIVIDE(CALCULATE(COUNTROWS(Fact_Sales), Fact_Sales[Attainment Flag] = 1), COUNTROWS(Fact_Sales), 0)
		formatString: 0.00%
		displayFolder: Performance KPIs
		lineageTag: baea5495-a3d3-42e3-a4dd-922a05b85bf3

	/// WHAT: The proportion of orders that are unprofitable (profit < 0).
	/// LOGIC: Count orders where profit < 0, divided by total order count.
	/// USE IN: KPI card (risk indicator), Loss-Making Orders stacked bar by category. This is a hidden value destruction alert — 28.9% of orders (579) destroy value totalling MYR -1.6M.
	/// RAG TARGET: Green <10%, Amber 10-25%, Red >25%.
	/// ACTION: Use this measure to trigger an alert email when the rate exceeds 25%.
	measure 'Loss Order %' = DIVIDE(CALCULATE(COUNTROWS(Fact_Sales), Fact_Sales[Profit] < 0), COUNTROWS(Fact_Sales), 0)
		formatString: 0.00%
		displayFolder: Performance KPIs
		lineageTag: ff4ac46e-b82f-46f2-8ad7-67c2804ffb6e

	/// WHAT: Average revenue generated per individual order.
	/// LOGIC: DIVIDE(Total Revenue, COUNTROWS(fact table)). Reflects deal quality and B2B nature of the business.
	/// USE IN: KPI card with MoM trend arrow, Sales Rep leaderboard (deal quality column). 2024 baseline = MYR 6,988. Use alongside Total Orders to distinguish between volume growth vs deal-size growth.
	/// TARGET: MYR 7,000 benchmark. A falling AOV with rising order count may indicate discount abuse.
	measure 'Avg Order Value' = DIVIDE([Total Revenue], COUNTROWS(Fact_Sales), 0)
		formatString: #,##0.00
		displayFolder: Financial KPIs
		lineageTag: b9401df8-0103-4799-bcdb-a06df3b7cc0b

	/// WHAT: Month-over-month revenue growth rate as a percentage.
	/// LOGIC: Compares current period [Total Revenue] to the same measure one month prior using DATEADD on the Date table. Returns 0 if prior month has no data.
	/// USE IN: KPI card trend arrow, sparkline on the Monthly Revenue card. Requires the Date table relationship to be active — will return blank if the Date slicer is set to a single day.
	/// IMPORTANT: This measure is context-sensitive. It works correctly when filtered to a month or month range. Avoid using in matrix rows without a date dimension on the axis.
	measure 'MoM Revenue Growth' =
			VAR currentRevenue = [Total Revenue]
			VAR lastMonthRevenue = CALCULATE([Total Revenue], DATEADD('Date'[Date], -1, MONTH))
			RETURN DIVIDE(currentRevenue - lastMonthRevenue, lastMonthRevenue, 0)
		formatString: 0.00%
		displayFolder: Performance KPIs
		lineageTag: fbda5ef1-01a2-4b7c-9482-416af5cb8945

	/// WHAT: Total actual revenue as a percentage of total target revenue.
	/// LOGIC: DIVIDE(Total Revenue, SUM(target_revenue)). Compares the aggregate revenue sum to the aggregate target sum — a different view from [Target Attainment %] which counts order-level hits.
	/// USE IN: Attainment gauge chart, KPI card. 2024 result = 95.4% — revenue is close to total target, but only 38.9% of individual orders hit their target. Show BOTH measures on the dashboard to reveal this nuance.
	/// RAG TARGET: Green >95%, Amber 85-95%, Red <85%.
	measure 'Revenue vs Target' = DIVIDE([Total Revenue], SUM(Fact_Sales[Target Revenue]), 0)
		formatString: 0.00%
		displayFolder: Performance KPIs
		lineageTag: 52b627b3-d884-4f8a-b30f-3365a3a5cdf0

	/// WHAT: Total revenue from orders that met or exceeded their target.
	/// LOGIC: Filters to rows where Attainment Flag = 1, then sums Revenue.
	/// USE IN: Funnel chart (Stage 2 of 3). Pair with [Total Revenue] as Stage 1 and [Profitable Revenue] as Stage 3.
	measure 'Revenue Hit Target' = CALCULATE(SUM(Fact_Sales[Revenue]), Fact_Sales[Attainment Flag] = 1)
		formatString: #,##0.00
		displayFolder: Financial KPIs
		lineageTag: 1031bf04-008d-4d10-a828-5a0f292c59b4

	/// WHAT: Total revenue from orders that generated a positive profit.
	/// LOGIC: Filters to rows where Profit > 0, then sums Revenue.
	/// USE IN: Funnel chart (Stage 3 of 3). Pair with [Total Revenue] as Stage 1 and [Revenue Hit Target] as Stage 2.
	measure 'Profitable Revenue' = CALCULATE(SUM(Fact_Sales[Revenue]), Fact_Sales[Profit] > 0)
		formatString: #,##0.00
		displayFolder: Financial KPIs
		lineageTag: 09475ee4-9ff7-4ea6-a908-91060a6c86c2

	column 'Order ID'
